{"annotations": [{"id": ["NCBIGene:1128"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "M1 Muscarinic receptors", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9753792881965637, "span": {"begin": 0, "end": 23}}, {"id": ["mesh:D011188"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "potassium", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9975663423538208, "span": {"begin": 52, "end": 61}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1128"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "M1 receptor", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9884198904037476, "span": {"begin": 131, "end": 142}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004827"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "epileptiform", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.7138850092887878, "span": {"begin": 212, "end": 224}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004827"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "epilepsy", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999772310256958, "span": {"begin": 343, "end": 351}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:39462"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "pilocarpine", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9988204836845398, "span": {"begin": 382, "end": 393}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002217"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "carbachol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9988356232643127, "span": {"begin": 398, "end": 407}}, {"id": ["mesh:D012640"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "seizures", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.8576643466949463, "span": {"begin": 478, "end": 486}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1128"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "M1 receptor", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.983739972114563, "span": {"begin": 505, "end": 516}}], "text": "M1 Muscarinic receptors are modulators of M-current potassium channel activity (Marrion, 1997). Blocking the M-current through the M1 receptor contributes to cell depolarization, which then leads to the start of epileptiform activity (Greget et al., 2016). The use of muscarinic agonists is well established and often used in animal models of epilepsy and include compounds such as pilocarpine and carbachol (Curia et al., 2008, Turski et al., 1983). It has been suggested that seizures initiated through M1 receptor activation occur when the ratio between glutamatergic and GABAergic activity reaches a threshold (Miller, 2015).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:15:24 +0000 2026"}